{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe `code_review` artifact (per Gerrit change/revision) persists findings today but is WRITE-ONLY: there is no reader analogous to plan-review's `latest_review_result`, and the payload records only a diff-text hash, not the reviewed code STATE. The novelty convergence gate needs (a) prior SURFACED findings to score against, and (b) a content-addressed record of what code was reviewed, addressable by a typed key.\n\n## What\n- Extend the `code_review_result_v1` payload (src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py `build_payload`) with:\n  - `session_id` as a TOP-LEVEL field (nullable; set for local reviews) so it is queryable,\n  - `deps`: a per-reviewed-file content-hash map `{path: sha256}`, computed by a thin code-review dep collector over changed_files that REUSES only the `attest._hash_file` primitive (NOT `dependency_hashes`, which is plan/ticket-coupled) (raw file-bytes sha256, with the `absent` sentinel so create/delete is detectable). Scope = the review's changed_files (and cited-file paths). Computed once in the gate (produce_code_review_verdict) so BOTH local and the Gerrit voter path get it via the existing emit.\n- Artifact addressing: local artifacts use title `code-review: session:{session_id}` (analogous to the Gerrit `code-review: {change_id} @ {revision}`); Gerrit unchanged.\n- Add a reader `latest_code_review_result(key)` (typed key: `session:<id>` or `change:<id>`) that resolves the artifact by title prefix, and returns the most-recent artifact's SURFACED findings (decision in {block, advisory}) plus its `deps` map. Mirror `latest_review_result`'s best-effort, never-raises, schema-guarded (`code_review_result_v1`), walk-back-over-unusable posture. SURFACED-ONLY is mandatory (see old-frilly-plankton) so dropped findings never re-enter the novelty prior set.\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py (payload + reader); the `deps` computation seam in produce_code_review_verdict.\n- Out of scope: local persistence wiring (paradoxal-balsamic-bubblefish), the region_gated_floor consumer (blameless-grindable-noctule).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `build_payload` records `session_id` (top-level) and a `{path: sha256}` deps map built by a code-review dep collector reusing `attest._hash_file` (not `dependency_hashes`).\n- [ ] Local artifacts are titled `code-review: session:{session_id}`; the reader resolves by title prefix for the typed key.\n- [ ] `latest_code_review_result(key)` returns SURFACED-only prior findings + the deps map; never raises; schema-guarded to `code_review_result_v1`.\n- [ ] Unit tests: surfaced-only filtering; typed-key isolation (a `session:` key never returns a `change:` artifact and vice versa); malformed/absent -> None.\n- [ ] The deps map is computed once in the gate and reaches both local and Gerrit emits."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783628602541900001,"uuid":"8a316c69-ceec-4d13-a820-c494d7ecef21"}